headline: KLA Corporation (KLAC) Stock Trades Up, Here Is Why
summary: Shares of semiconductor manufacturing equipment maker KLA Corporation (NASDAQ:KLAC) jumped 4.4% in the afternoon session after analysts at Stifel and BofA Securities raised their price targets on the stock, signaling strong confidence in the semiconductor equipment maker. Stifel increased its price target to $1,050 from $922, while BofA Securities adjusted its target to $1,300 from $1,000, with both firms maintaining their 'Buy' ratings.
